00:00:10.740 --> 00:00:11.640
Explanation.

00:00:12.060 --> 00:00:14.970
So what on earth is a headquarters?

00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:20.430
Think of it as the main control room,
the brain, the administrative nerve

00:00:20.430 --> 00:00:23.190
center of any big short organization.

00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:25.200
Company or institution.

00:00:25.680 --> 00:00:29.370
It's the location where all the
important decisions are made.

00:00:29.520 --> 00:00:35.190
The top bosses sit and all the key
operations are managed for your exam.

00:00:35.340 --> 00:00:39.180
Remembering the headquarters of
various national and international

00:00:39.180 --> 00:00:44.910
organizations, banks and regulatory
bodies is absolutely critical because

00:00:44.970 --> 00:00:47.135
they love asking these factual questions.

00:00:47.855 --> 00:00:50.795
It's like free marks if
you just remember them.

00:00:51.245 --> 00:00:54.365
Real world relevance
and why should you care?

00:00:54.695 --> 00:00:58.775
Well, knowing the headquarters of
financial institutions helps you

00:00:58.775 --> 00:01:03.215
understand their global footprint and
where their power is concentrated.

00:01:03.595 --> 00:01:07.765
This is super important for dealing
with any of their operations.

00:01:08.125 --> 00:01:12.535
It also gives you a clearer picture
of the regulatory world and the big

00:01:12.535 --> 00:01:16.705
players who govern the financial
sector, which directly impacts how

00:01:16.705 --> 00:01:19.045
we understand compliance and policy.

