Now, how will they try to trick
you with headquarters questions in

00:02:27.870 --> 00:02:32.520
the general awareness section, it's
mainly a memory game, so don't worry.

00:02:32.880 --> 00:02:34.350
Based on past papers.

00:02:34.410 --> 00:02:35.670
Here are the formats.

00:02:36.025 --> 00:02:39.715
About 60% of the time,
it'll be a direct question.

00:02:39.894 --> 00:02:44.515
Just as straightforward, where is
the headquarters of X, Y, Z located?

00:02:44.815 --> 00:02:48.745
For example, where is the headquarters
of the World Bank located?

00:02:49.225 --> 00:02:52.375
Around 25% of the time you'll see a match.

00:02:52.375 --> 00:02:57.084
The following question, they'll give you
two columns, one with organizations and

00:02:57.084 --> 00:03:02.334
the other with cities, and you have to
play matchmaker, for instance, match RBI

00:03:02.334 --> 00:03:05.185
with Mumbai and IMF with Washington, DC.

00:03:05.590 --> 00:03:09.280
Then for about 10% of
questions, it's an odd one out.

00:03:09.640 --> 00:03:13.450
They'll give you a list and you have
to find the one that doesn't belong.

00:03:13.600 --> 00:03:17.560
Maybe because all others are
headquartered in the same city, for

00:03:17.560 --> 00:03:21.970
example, which of the following does
not have its headquarters in Geneva?

00:03:22.359 --> 00:03:27.100
And finally, the rarest type at 5%
is the statement based question.

00:03:27.399 --> 00:03:31.089
They'll give you a statement about
an organization and its headquarters

00:03:31.209 --> 00:03:33.250
and ask if it's true or false.

00:03:33.665 --> 00:03:35.195
Formulas and tricks.

00:03:35.525 --> 00:03:39.305
Since this topic is all about
facts, there are no mathematical

00:03:39.305 --> 00:03:41.255
formulas, thank goodness, right?

00:03:41.645 --> 00:03:46.565
Instead, we focus on smart memory
aids, or as we call it, jugar.

00:03:46.985 --> 00:03:52.085
You can use acronyms of phrases
by creating memorable lines or try

00:03:52.085 --> 00:03:57.005
association linking an organization to
a feature of its city, like thinking

00:03:57.005 --> 00:03:59.225
Geneva for global organizations.

00:03:59.590 --> 00:04:02.380
A very powerful method is categorization.

00:04:02.679 --> 00:04:06.850
Just group, all organizations
by their headquarter city, all

00:04:06.850 --> 00:04:10.480
Geneva ones together, all New
York ones, all Mumbai ones.

00:04:10.810 --> 00:04:14.950
Visual memory can also help use
maps to mentally place these HQs.

00:04:15.530 --> 00:04:20.300
And if you're the creative type, making
up short rhymes or songs can really make

00:04:20.300 --> 00:04:23.330
the information stick methods of solving.

00:04:23.599 --> 00:04:26.840
So when a question appears,
how do you tackle it?

00:04:27.200 --> 00:04:29.390
The best approach is direct recall.

00:04:29.570 --> 00:04:33.349
If you see the question and the
answer pops into your head, brilliant.

00:04:33.530 --> 00:04:34.580
That's the fastest way.

00:04:35.210 --> 00:04:39.140
If your brain is taking a little
nap, use the elimination strategy.

00:04:39.320 --> 00:04:42.950
Look at the options, and kick out
the ones you know for sure are wrong.

00:04:43.130 --> 00:04:46.310
This seriously increases your
chances of getting it right.

00:04:46.700 --> 00:04:51.680
You can also do a categorical check if
you've memorized organizations by city.

00:04:51.770 --> 00:04:54.920
Mentally run through your list
for each city in the options.

00:04:55.220 --> 00:04:57.620
Sometimes keyword association helps.

